**Code Explanation:**

The code implements the data pipeline and trains the Super-Resolution Denoising Autoencoder (SR-DAE). 1. Data Splitting: It identifies the top 5% most massive cluster patches by finding the maximum tSZ Compton-y value per patch. These 76 patches are strictly withheld from the training and validation sets and placed into the test set to prevent data leakage. The remaining 1447 patches are split into 70% training (1066 patches), 15% validation (228 patches), and the rest go to the test set. The indices are saved to data/splits.npz. 2. Data Loader: A custom PyTorch Dataset (CompSepDataset) is implemented to load the 6-frequency stacked maps, sample SO and Planck noise on the fly, and load the ground truth tSZ and CIB maps. It uses mmap_mode='r' to efficiently read from the large .npy files without loading everything into RAM. 3. Normalization: Before training, the pipeline computes the mean and standard deviation of the 6-channel observations over a subset of the training data. These statistics are used to normalize the inputs to zero mean and unit variance, and are saved to data/normalization_stats.npz. The target tSZ maps are scaled by 10^6 to ensure numerical stability during training. 4. Architecture: The SR-DAE is implemented as a multi-scale U-Net with two separate encoders: one for the SO LAT channels (90, 150, 217 GHz) and one for the Planck channels (353, 545, 857 GHz). The decoder reconstructs the tSZ map from the SO features while utilizing a GatedCrossAttention mechanism at every scale to incorporate spatial information from the Planck (CIB-dominated) features. 5. Loss Function: The composite loss function consists of: L_L1: Pixel-wise L1 loss between the prediction and the scaled ground truth tSZ. L_spec: A custom differentiable PyTorch module (PowerSpectrumLoss) that computes the 2D power spectrum of the unscaled prediction, bins it into 1D exactly like utils.powers(), and penalizes the squared difference of the log power spectra relative to the mean ground truth power spectrum. It applies an ell^3 weighting to emphasize high-frequency baryonic feedback. L_corr: A differentiable normalized cross-correlation penalty (ncc_loss) that forces the reconstruction residual to be orthogonal to the input CIB maps. 6. Training: The model is trained for 20 epochs using the AdamW optimizer and a ReduceLROnPlateau scheduler. Progress and key metrics are printed concisely. Finally, the trained weights and loss history are saved to the data/ directory.

**Modifications:**

Changed num_workers=8 to num_workers=0 in all DataLoader instances to fix the RuntimeError: unable to allocate shared memory(shm) error. This avoids using multiprocessing for data loading, which was exceeding the Docker container's shared memory limit. Added detailed print statements during the training loop to ensure the researcher has access to the final loss values and metrics.

