**Code Explanation:**

This script performs the final uncertainty calibration and scientific validation of the Conditional Diffusion Model (CDM) and Super-Resolution Denoising Autoencoder (SR-DAE) against the linear baselines (cILC and Wiener Filter). 1. Linear Baselines Re-evaluation: It recomputes the cILC weights and Wiener Filter (WF) 2D harmonic space filters using the training set patches. It then evaluates these linear baselines on the test set to ensure a fair comparison with the CDM and DAE models. 2. Power Spectra and Transfer Function: It calculates the cross-power spectra between the reconstructed maps and the true tSZ maps to compute the Transfer Function T(l) = C_l^{pred x true} / C_l^{true x true}. 3. Reconstruction Gain: It computes the reconstruction gain as the ratio of the residual power spectrum of the cILC baseline to the residual power spectrum of the models (C_l^{res, cILC} / C_l^{res, model}) for the multipole range l in [1000, 5000]. 4. Y_SZ-M Relation: It extracts the integrated Compton-y parameter (Y_SZ) by summing the tSZ signal over each patch and uses the peak true tSZ signal as a mass proxy (M). It then calculates the bias and scatter of the fractional error for each model. 5. Probability Integral Transform (PIT): It validates the CDM uncertainty calibration by computing the PIT values for the true tSZ pixels under the predicted Gaussian distribution (using the CDM mean and variance maps). A well-calibrated model should yield a uniform PIT distribution between 0 and 1 (mean approx 0.5, std approx 0.2887). 6. Consolidated Figure: It generates a 4-panel figure containing the PIT histogram, the Y_SZ-M scatter plot, the Transfer Function T(l), and the Reconstruction Gain Ratio, saving it at high resolution.

